               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490129-name-832" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490129-name-832" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490129-name-832" type="surname" value="AMERY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490129-name-832" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM AMERY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am captain of the barge <hi rend="italic">Worsley</hi>, in the London Docks. On 14th Jan., at eight o'clock in the evening, I was in Wellington-street, Southwark—I felt something, missed my handkerchief, and saw the prisoner crossing the road close to me—he put his hand in his breast—I collared him, and told him he had got my handkerchief—he denied it, and, while struggling to get away, threw it into the street—I picked it up, and. gave him in charge—there was no one else near enough to have taken it.</p>
               <p>
